main event: A Norwegian pilot reported sighting a projectile flying across the Swedish coast, disappearing over the horizon into Norway.
interesting points: The object was traveling at an altitude of 20,000 feet and disappeared in four seconds., The object emitted a bluish-green flame and left no trail in the sky., The sighting emphasized that the object could have been a meteor, rocket, or guided missile., The incident bears similarity to other documented sightings (#145 and #133)., Swedish Air Defense concluded no proof exists of unidentified flying objects passing over Sweden despite various reports.
